  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "At the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs), students pursuing various programs, such as integrated BS-MS, PhD, or other research-based courses, may have access to fellowships. However, whether every student receives a fellowship can depend on several factors, including the specific program, their academic performance, and the availability of funds.\n\nFor PhD students, fellowships are often provided by the institute or may be linked to government grants, and they typically receive a monthly stipend. For BS-MS students, fellowships may not be universally provided, as these programs often focus on undergraduate education, and students may need to apply for internships or research projects for financial support.\n\nIt's best to consult the specific IISER you are interested in or refer to their official website for detailed information about fellowship availability and eligibility criteria for different programs.",
